Figure 5. Free energy profiles of hydration of nanopores with different geometries and lid configurations. (A) PMFs of hydration for a set of
nanopores with and without a lid and/or tilt (see Figure S1). The circles mark the theoretical ΔGdewet as calculated using eq 3. The pores with 0° tilt, lid (orange), 20° tilt, narrow lid (red), and 20° tilt, wide lid (purple), did not have well-defined hydrated minima, so their locations were
estimated by using the Nwater of the corresponding pore without the lid, denoted with a vertical dashed line (see Methods for details). (B) Correlation of dewetting ΔGs calculated using eq 3 (theoretical) with those derived from the PMFs (simulation). The dashed line marks the ideal
